CONTRIBUTING.md
     3вҶ’# Contributing вҖҰ
     5вҶ’## Code of Conduct
     7вҶ’All interactions in the **npm** organization on GitHub are considered to be covered by our standard [Code of Conduct](https://docs.npmjs.com/policies/conduct).
     8вҶ’
     9вҶ’## Reporting Bugs
    11вҶ’Before submitting a new bug report please search for an existing or similar report.
    12вҶ’
    13вҶ’Use one of our existing issue templates if you believe you've come across a unique problem.
    14вҶ’
    15вҶ’Duplicate issues, or issues that don't use one of our templates may get closed without a response.
    16вҶ’
    17вҶ’## Pull Request Conventions
    19вҶ’### Commits
    21вҶ’We use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/).
    22вҶ’
    23вҶ’When opening a pull request please be sure that either the pull request title, or each commit in the pull request, has one of the following prefixes:
    24вҶ’
    25вҶ’ - `feat`: For when introducing a new feature.  The result will be a new semver minor version of the package when it is next published.
    26вҶ’ - `fix`: For bug fixes. The result will be a new semver patch version of the package when it is next published.
    27вҶ’ - `docs`: For documentation updates.  The result will be a new semver patch version of the package when it is next published.
    28вҶ’ - `chore`: For changes that do not affect the published module.  Often these are changes to tests.  The result will be *no* change to the version of the package when it is next published (as the commit does not affect the published version).
    29вҶ’
    30вҶ’### Test Coverage
    32вҶ’Pull requests made against this repo will run `npm test` automatically.  Please make sure tests pass locally before submitting a PR.
    33вҶ’
    34вҶ’Every new feature or bug fix should come with a corresponding test or tests that validate the solutions. Testing also reports on code coverage and will fail if code coverage drops.
    35вҶ’
    36вҶ’### Linting
    38вҶ’Linting is also done automatically once tests pass.  `npm run lintfix` will fix most linting errors automatically.
    39вҶ’
    40вҶ’Please make sure linting passes before submitting a PR.
    41вҶ’
    42вҶ’## What _not_ to contribute?
    44вҶ’### Dependencies
    46вҶ’It should be noted that our team does not accept third-party dependency updates/PRs.  If you submit a PR trying to update our dependencies we will close it with or without a reference to these contribution guidelines.
    47вҶ’
    48вҶ’### Tools/Automation
    50вҶ’Our core team is responsible for the maintenance of the tooling/automation in this project and we ask contributors to not make changes to these when contributing (e.g. `.github/*`, `.eslintrc.json`, `.licensee.json`).  Most of those files also have a header at the top to remind folks they are automatically generated.  Pull requests that alter these will not be accepted.
README.md
     4вҶ’## Note
     6вҶ’-   Sections are treated as nested objects.
     7вҶ’
     8вҶ’-   Section-less items are treated as globals.
     9вҶ’
    10вҶ’## Usage
    12вҶ’Consider an INI file such as the following:
    13вҶ’
    14вҶ’```ini
    15вҶ’; This comment is being ignored
    16вҶ’scope = global
    17вҶ’
    18вҶ’[database]
    19вҶ’user = dbuser
    20вҶ’password = dbpassword
    21вҶ’database = use_this_database
    22вҶ’
    23вҶ’[paths.default]
    24вҶ’datadir = /var/lib/data
    25вҶ’array[] = first value
    26вҶ’array[] = second value
    27вҶ’array[] = third value
    28вҶ’```
    29вҶ’
    30вҶ’You can **read**, **modify** and **write** it like so:
    31вҶ’
    32вҶ’```js
    33вҶ’import { writeFile , readFile } from 'node:fs/promises'
    34вҶ’import { stringify , parse } from 'ini'
    35вҶ’
    36вҶ’//  Read INI file as text
    37вҶ’
    38вҶ’let text = await readFile(`./Original.ini`,{
    39вҶ’    encoding : 'utf-8'
    40вҶ’})
    41вҶ’
    42вҶ’//  Parse text data to object
    43вҶ’
    44вҶ’const config = parse(text)
    45вҶ’
    46вҶ’//  Modify data object
    47вҶ’
    48вҶ’config.scope = 'local'
    49вҶ’config.database.database = 'use_another_database'
    50вҶ’config.paths.default.tmpdir = '/tmp'
    51вҶ’delete config.paths.default.datadir
    52вҶ’config.paths.default.array.push('fourth value')
    53вҶ’
    54вҶ’//  Stringify data object
    55вҶ’
    56вҶ’text = stringify(config,{ 
    57вҶ’    section : 'section' 
    58вҶ’})
    59вҶ’
    60вҶ’//  Write INI file as text
    61вҶ’
    62вҶ’await writeFile(`./Modified.ini`,text)
    63вҶ’```
    64вҶ’
    65вҶ’The written file will contain the following:
    66вҶ’
    67вҶ’```ini
    68вҶ’[section]
    69вҶ’scope=local
    70вҶ’[section.database]
    71вҶ’user=dbuser
    72вҶ’password=dbpassword
    73вҶ’database=use_another_database
    74вҶ’[section.paths.default]
    75вҶ’tmpdir=/tmp
    76вҶ’array[]=first value
    77вҶ’array[]=second value
    78вҶ’array[]=third value
    79вҶ’array[]=fourth value
    80вҶ’```
    81вҶ’
    82вҶ’## API
    84вҶ’### Parse
    86вҶ’Attempts to turn the given INI string into a nested data object.
    87вҶ’
    88вҶ’```js
    89вҶ’// You can also use `decode`
    90вҶ’const object = parse(`<INI Text>`) 
    91вҶ’```
    92вҶ’
    93вҶ’### Stringify
    95вҶ’Encodes the given data object as an INI formatted string.
    96вҶ’
    97вҶ’```js
    98вҶ’// You can also use `encode`
    99вҶ’stringify(object,{
   100вҶ’
   101вҶ’    /**
   102вҶ’     *  Whether to insert spaces before & after `=`
   103вҶ’     * 
   104вҶ’     *  Disabled by default to have better 
   105вҶ’     *  compatibility with old picky parsers.
   106вҶ’     */
   107вҶ’
   108вҶ’    whitespace : false ,
   109вҶ’
   110вҶ’    /**
   111вҶ’     *  Whether to align the `=` character for each section.
   112вҶ’     *  -> Also enables the `whitespace` option
   113вҶ’     */
   114вҶ’
   115вҶ’    align : false ,
   116вҶ’
   117вҶ’    /**
   118вҶ’     *  Identifier to use for global items 
   119вҶ’     *  and to prepend to all other sections.
   120вҶ’     */
   121вҶ’
   122вҶ’    section ,
   123вҶ’
   124вҶ’    /**
   125вҶ’     *  Whether to sort all sections & their keys alphabetically.
   126вҶ’     */
   127вҶ’
   128вҶ’    sort : false ,
   129вҶ’
   130вҶ’    /**
   131вҶ’     *  Whether to insert a newline after each section header.
   132вҶ’     * 
   133вҶ’     *  The TOSHIBA & FlashAir parser require this format. 
   134вҶ’     */
   135вҶ’
   136вҶ’    newline : false ,
   137вҶ’
   138вҶ’    /**
   139вҶ’     *  Which platforms line-endings should be used.
   140вҶ’     * 
   141вҶ’     *  win32 -> CR+LF
   142вҶ’     *  other -> LF
   143вҶ’     * 
   144вҶ’     *  Default is the current platform
   145вҶ’     */
   146вҶ’
   147вҶ’    platform ,
   148вҶ’
   149вҶ’    /**
   150вҶ’     *  Whether to append `[]` to array keys.
   151вҶ’     * 
   152вҶ’     *  Some parsers treat duplicate names by themselves as arrays
   153вҶ’     */
   154вҶ’
   155вҶ’    bracketedArray : true
   156вҶ’
   157вҶ’})
   158вҶ’```
   159вҶ’
   160вҶ’*For backwards compatibility any string passed as the*  
   161вҶ’*options parameter is treated as the `section` option.*
   162вҶ’
   163вҶ’```js
   164вҶ’stringify(object,'section')
   165вҶ’```
   166вҶ’
   167вҶ’### Un / Escape
   169вҶ’Turn the given string into a safe to  
   170вҶ’use key or value in your INI file.
   171вҶ’
   172вҶ’```js
   173вҶ’safe(`"unsafe string"`) // -> \"unsafe string\"
   174вҶ’```
   175вҶ’
   176вҶ’Or reverse the process with:
   177вҶ’
   178вҶ’```js
   179вҶ’unsafe(`\\"safe string\\"`) // -> "safe string"
   180вҶ’```
